    public interface ListEntry
extends CompositeEntry<List<?>>
    The interface represents list entry. Lists are encoded as follows: l<bencoded values>e. The initial l and trailing e are beginning and ending delimiters. Lists may contain any bencoded type, including integers, strings, dictionaries, and even lists within other lists.

    Example: l4:spam4:eggse represents the list of two strings: [ "spam", "eggs" ] Example: le represents an empty list: []
